==Speaking to the mage in the Chaos Temple==
* '''Mage of Zamorak:''' Ah, you again. The Wilderness is hardly the appropriate place for a conversation now, is it? What was it you wanted?
* '''Player:''' Err... I didn't really want anything.
* '''Mage of Zamorak:''' So why did you approach me?
* '''Player:''' I was just wondering why you sell runes in the Wilderness?
* '''Mage of Zamorak:''' Well I can't go doing it in the middle of Varrock, can I? In case you hadn't noticed, I'm a servant of Zamorak. The Saradominists have made sure that people like me are not welcome in these parts.
* {{topt|Where do you get your runes from?}}
** '''Player:''' Where do you get your runes from?
** '''Mage of Zamorak:''' Well we craft them of course.
** '''Player:''' We?
** '''Mage of Zamorak:''' My associates and I. Despite the best attempts of the Saradominists, there's still more of us around than they'd like.
** '''Player:''' I can't imagine they like you crafting runes much. Do they not try and stop you?
** '''Mage of Zamorak:''' Ha! I'm sure they'd love to, but we have methods of runecrafting that they can only dream of!
** '''Player:''' Care to share?
** '''Mage of Zamorak:''' Why would I? You are not a member of our institute. How do I know you won't just go and share all of our secrets with those Saradominist fools in the Order of Wizards.
** {{topt|Maybe I could make it worth your while?}}
*** '''Player:''' Maybe I could make it worth your while?
*** '''Mage of Zamorak:''' How? What do you have to offer?
*** '''Player:''' Well what is it you want?
*** '''Mage of Zamorak:''' Until recently, our runecrafting secrets allowed us to produce runes at a far superior rate compared to the inept Order of Wizards, but something has changed.
*** '''Mage of Zamorak:''' From what we can gather, they've somehow rediscovered how to access the lost Rune Essence Mine.
*** '''Player:''' Ah, well I know all about that. I was actually the one to help them do it!
*** '''Mage of Zamorak:''' You did what? You helped the Order of Wizards?
*** '''Player:''' Err...
*** {{topt|Yes, but I can still help you as well.}}
**** '''Player:''' Yes, but I can still help you as well.
**** '''Mage of Zamorak:''' So you're a mercenary with no allegiance? Not the type I like working with, but if you have knowledge of the Rune Essence Mine, I seemingly have little choice.
**** '''Mage of Zamorak:''' Alright, if you help us access the Rune Essence Mine, we will share our runecrafting secrets with you in return.
**** {{tact|below}}
*** {{topt|I did it so that I could then steal their secrets.}}
**** '''Player:''' I did it so that I could then steal their secrets.
**** '''Mage of Zamorak:''' You did? Perhaps I underestimated you.
**** '''Mage of Zamorak:''' Alright, if you help us access the Rune Essence Mine, we will share our runecrafting secrets with you in return.
**** {{topt|Deal.}}
***** '''Player:''' Deal.
***** '''Mage of Zamorak:''' Good. Now, all I need from you is the spell that will teleport me to the Rune Essence Mine.
***** '''Player:''' Err... I don't actually know the spell.
***** '''Mage of Zamorak:''' What? Then how do you get there.
***** '''Player:''' Oh, well the people who do know the spell just teleport me there directly.
***** '''Mage of Zamorak:''' Hmm... I see. That makes this slightly more complex, but no matter. You can still help us.
***** '''Player:''' How?
***** '''Mage of Zamorak:''' I'll give you a scrying orb with a standard cypher spell cast upon it. The orb will absorb mystical energies that it is exposed to.
***** '''Mage of Zamorak:''' If you teleport to the Rune Essence Mine from three different locations, the orb will absorb the energies of the spell and allow us to reverse-engineer the magic behind it.
***** '''Mage of Zamorak:''' Do you know of three different people who can teleport you there?
***** '''Player:''' Maybe?
***** '''Mage of Zamorak:''' Well if not, I'm sure one of those fools in the Order of Wizards can tell you. Now, here's the orb.
